result.execSummary:
The defendant Kuristina L Harris was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Intimidate Witness [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.42.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant pleads GUILTY to the amended Count 1.  Defendant examined as to her plea, advised of her Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived her rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. 
Sentencing proceeded.   Statements made as to sentencing.   
Court ordered defendant to serve 59 days in the House of Correction, with 59 days credit for time served.  TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.
Court order $500.00 fine inclusive of costs and inclusive of the DNA surcharge.  Cash bail to be applied.
Appeal rights given.
